This program downloads the html and css code of a website input by the user.
The program has been written in Linux OS and not yet been tested for other platforms.

Author: Ulas A.
Date: 5 Oct 2016
Python version written with: 3.4 

This program takes a web page URL in the form of www.yourwebsite/ and retrieves the html code of the front page.

The program will currently not work if http:// or https:// is input as part of the path.

The program creates folders Pages and CSS. The main page is stored in Pages and all the .css files obtaind from
the main page are retrieved in the CSS folder. Next time the program is run the existing folders are deleted and 
re-written by the program. 











